msgctxt "sn35.104:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 35 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 35 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn35.104:0.2"
msgid "11. Yogakkhemivagga "
msgstr "11. Sanctuary "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn35.104:0.3"
msgid "104. Yogakkhemisutta "
msgstr "104. Sanctuary "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli4.85, sc1
msgctxt "sn35.104:1.1"
msgid "Sāvatthinidānaṃ. "
msgstr "At Sāvatthī. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn35.104:1.2"
msgid "“Yogakkhemipariyāyaṃ vo, bhikkhave, dhammapariyāyaṃ desessāmi. "
msgstr "“Mendicants, I will teach you an exposition of the teaching, an explanation of one who has reached sanctuary. "

msgctxt "sn35.104:1.3"
msgid "Taṃ suṇātha. "
msgstr "Listen … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn35.104:1.4"
msgid "Katamo ca, bhikkhave, yogakkhemipariyāyo dhammapariyāyo? "
msgstr "And what is an exposition of the teaching, an explanation of one who has reached sanctuary? "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn35.104:1.5"
msgid "Santi, bhikkhave, cakkhuviññeyyā rūpā iṭṭhā kantā manāpā piyarūpā kāmūpasaṃhitā rajanīyā. "
msgstr "There are sights known by the eye that are likable, desirable, agreeable, pleasant, sensual, and arousing. "

msgctxt "sn35.104:1.6"
msgid "Te tathāgatassa pahīnā ucchinnamūlā tālāvatthukatā anabhāvaṅkatā āyatiṃ anuppādadhammā. "
msgstr "The Realized One has given these up, cut them off at the root, made them like a palm stump, and obliterated them, so they are unable to arise in the future. "

# NOTE: See BB’s notes on the pun involved here. I don’t attempt to retain the pun.
msgctxt "sn35.104:1.7"
msgid "Tesañca pahānāya akkhāsi yogaṃ, tasmā tathāgato ‘yogakkhemī’ti vuccati … pe … "
msgstr "He teaches meditation for giving them up. That’s why the Realized One is called one who has reached sanctuary. … "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn35.104:1.8"
msgid "santi, bhikkhave, manoviññeyyā dhammā iṭṭhā kantā manāpā piyarūpā kāmūpasaṃhitā rajanīyā. "
msgstr "There are thoughts known by the mind that are likable, desirable, agreeable, pleasant, sensual, and arousing. "

msgctxt "sn35.104:1.9"
msgid "Te tathāgatassa pahīnā ucchinnamūlā tālāvatthukatā anabhāvaṅkatā āyatiṃ anuppādadhammā. "
msgstr "The Realized One has given these up, cut them off at the root, made them like a palm stump, and obliterated them, so they are unable to arise in the future. "

msgctxt "sn35.104:1.10"
msgid "Tesañca pahānāya akkhāsi yogaṃ, tasmā tathāgato ‘yogakkhemī’ti vuccati. "
msgstr "He teaches meditation for giving them up. That’s why the Realized One is called one who has reached sanctuary. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn35.104:1.11"
msgid "Ayaṃ kho, bhikkhave, yogakkhemipariyāyo dhammapariyāyo”ti. "
msgstr "This is an exposition of the teaching, an explanation of one who has reached sanctuary.” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn35.104:1.12"
msgid "Paṭhamaṃ. "
msgstr ""

